[3] CTI: 1_AA23-341A.txt - “spear-phishing campaigns... leverage post-exploitation shells to escalate and move laterally”  
[4] KNOWN: `conhost.exe` is routinely abused to host malicious cmd/powershell instances without visible console windows

辩护律师论据（良性解释）：
`cmd.exe → conhost.exe` 的 `FORK` 事件是 Windows 控制台子系统标准行为，**完全良性**。`conhost.exe` 是 Windows 自 Vista 起引入的控制台主机进程，由 `cmd.exe`（或 `powershell.exe`、`bash.exe` 等）在启动交互式命令行会话时自动派生，用于隔离 UI 渲染与命令处理器逻辑，提升安全性和稳定性 [1]。该行为与已确认的恶意链（如 `cKfGW.exe → cmd.exe`）无直接父子关系——此处 `cmd.exe` 是合法父进程，而非被恶意载荷派生的子进程；且 `conhost.exe` 未参与任何后续恶意网络通信、文件写入或凭证窃取活动 [2]。在当前上下文中，该事件属于系统正常启动/用户打开命令提示符的常规路径，不构成攻击证据 [3]。

📚 来源：  
[1] KNOWN: Windows Console Host architecture — `conhost.exe` is spawned by console applications to host the console window  
[2] MITRE: T1059.003 (Windows Command Shell) — legitimate use does not imply abuse; no associated malicious command_line or network activity observed here  
[3] KNOWN: Standard Windows process tree includes `cmd.exe → conhost.exe` for every interactive cmd session, independent of malware presence

